VETERAN Umhlobo Wenene FM sports presenter Loyiso Sitsheke has died. 'Ta Lloyd' as he was affectionally known was part of the station's award-winning drive time show Masigoduke which is hosted by Amaza Ntshanga and Zizo Tshwete. He also hosted his own sports show Ã‰zemidlalo on weeknights. Station manager Phumzile Mnci announced the news during the show's last hour today. It is not clear what happened to ta Lloyd but he was on the show yesterday. Radio presenter Thabiso Mosia sent a tribute on his Twitter page saying he used to moonlight as a producer of ta Lloyd's show.  